I have this Rust code that takes a Vec<Person> and builds a HashMap<String, Vec<Person>> grouped by department. Can you review it and make it more idiomatic? Also, I'm seeing a lot of .clone() calls — is there a way to avoid them?

```rust
fn group_by_department(people: &Vec<Person>) -> HashMap<String, Vec<Person>> {
    let mut map: HashMap<String, Vec<Person>> = HashMap::new();
    for i in 0..people.len() {
        let person = people[i].clone();
        let dept = person.department.clone();
        if map.contains_key(&dept) {
            let mut list = map.get(&dept).unwrap().clone();
            list.push(person.clone());
            map.insert(dept.clone(), list);
        } else {
            map.insert(dept.clone(), vec![person.clone()]);
        }
    }
    return map;
}
```
